metadata.name: Epiphany
metadata.description:
"In a chaotic world we turn to nature to see the light"

---

It began with a walk in the woods to escape the world for a moment, 
and ended with an epiphany…

Mushrooms and ferns have superpowers; running superhighways beneath our feet, they grow where nothing else will, have psychotropic effects and will outlast us by millennia. 

Beautiful and magical yet feed on decay. When humans leave the planet these are the plants that will thrive in our wake, nourished by our bodies. 

This is the moment, the epiphany. It isn’t too late to learn.
